---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/docs-layout.astro";

const configCode = `import { defineHyprPayConfig } from "@hyprpay/cli";
import { hyprpay } from "./src/hyprpay";

export default defineHyprPayConfig({
  hyprpay,
  databaseUrl: process.env.DATABASE_URL,
});`;
---
<DocsLayout
  title="CLI"
  description="Use the CLI to initialize a project, apply Postgres schema changes, sync catalog versions, and validate deploy readiness."
  active="cli"
>
  <section class="steps">
    <article class="step">
      <span class="step-number">1</span>
      <h3>Initialize</h3>
      <pre><code>bunx hyprpay init</code></pre>
      <p>Creates a starter config and shows the expected Postgres + catalog wiring.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="step">
      <span class="step-number">2</span>
      <h3>Configure</h3>
      <pre><code>{configCode}</code></pre>
    </article>
    <article class="step">
      <span class="step-number">3</span>
      <h3>Push before deploy</h3>
      <pre><code>bunx hyprpay push -y && bun run build</code></pre>
      <p>The command applies idempotent Postgres setup and stores immutable catalog versions before the new app code starts serving traffic.</p>
    </article>
    <article class="step">
      <span class="step-number">4</span>
      <h3>Check status in CI</h3>
      <pre><code>bunx hyprpay status --throw</code></pre>
      <p>Use this to fail fast when config, store, or catalog sync is not ready.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <h2>Telemetry</h2>
  <p>CLI telemetry is off by default. It sends operational events through evlog to PostHog only when explicitly enabled.</p>
  <pre><code>HYPERPAY_TELEMETRY=1 POSTHOG_API_KEY=phc_... bunx hyprpay status</code></pre>
  <p>Explicit opt-out always wins: <code>HYPERPAY_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=1</code>, <code>HYPRPAY_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=1</code>, or <code>DO_NOT_TRACK=1</code>.</p>
</DocsLayout>
